{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888592331,"sessionID":"ses_284cacf3fffe6Xn9b7u593hknQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3563c0001H0B8EQGGq2krUp","messageID":"msg_d7b3558f3001utLao2y5hKzt0V","sessionID":"ses_284cacf3fffe6Xn9b7u593hknQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\nAR-001/\nAR-002/\nAR-003/\nAR-004/\nAR-005/\nAR-006/\nAR-007/\nAR-008/\nAR-009/\nAR-010/\nAR-011/\nAR-012/\nAR-013/\nAR-014/\nAR-015/\nAR-016/\nAR-017/\nAR-018/\nAR-019/\nAR-020/\nAR-021/\n\n(21 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"AR-001/\nAR-002/\nAR-003/\nAR-004/\nAR-005/\nAR-006/\nAR-007/\nAR-008/\nAR-009/\nAR-010/\nAR-011/\nAR-012/\nAR-013/\nAR-014/\nAR-015/\nAR-016/\nAR-017/\nAR-018/\nAR-019/\nAR-020/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes","time":{"start":1775888592322,"end":1775888592330}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888592353,"sessionID":"ses_284cacf3fffe6Xn9b7u593hknQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3568a80015ItfwTtuc2VlWi","messageID":"msg_d7b3558f3001utLao2y5hKzt0V","sessionID":"ses_284cacf3fffe6Xn9b7u593hknQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec-cli-build.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec-cli-build.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-021  \n6: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: The `build` command is responsible for building container images from packaged agent workspaces. It supports both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds, with automatic version increment and metadata management.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: CLI Build Options\n17: \n18: The system SHALL expose a `build` subcommand with configurable options for workspace path, proxy settings, cloud provider selection, and output directory.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build with default options\n21: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n22: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build` without any options\n23: - **THEN** the command SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`, show_default=True); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`, `Optional[str]`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`, `Optional[str]`); `output` = `None` (`--output`, `Optional[str]`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Build with custom workspace path\n26: - **GIVEN** a valid agent workspace exists at `/path/to/agent`\n27: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build -f /path/to/agent`\n28: - **THEN** the system SHALL resolve the workspace to the provided absolute path and proceed with the build\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Build with proxy configuration\n31: - **GIVEN** the user needs to use a custom proxy for dependency resolution\n32: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build -p http://proxy.example.com:8080`\n33: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass the proxy URL to `BuildRuntime.build()` as `proxy` option\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Build with cloud provider\n36: - **GIVEN** the metadata `build_mode` is set to `cloud`\n37: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build --cloud-provider huawei`\n38: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass the cloud provider name to `BuildRuntime._build_cloud()` for cloud-specific build orchestration\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Build with output directory\n41: - **GIVEN** the user wants build artifacts in a specific location\n42: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build --output /custom/output/dir`\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass the output path to `BuildRuntime.build()` and ensure the directory exists\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Build with verbose logging\n46: - **GIVEN** the user wants detailed build output\n47: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build --verbose`\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL set verbose mode on `BuildRuntime` and log detailed progress information\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: Build Mode Resolution\n53: \n54: The system SHALL determine the build mode from metadata, supporting both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Local build mode (default)\n57: - **GIVEN** the `agent_metadata.yaml` contains `build_mode: local` or no build_mode specified\n58: - **WHEN** `build` command executes\n59: - **THEN** the system SHALL invoke `BuildRuntime._build_local()` to build the Docker image locally\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Cloud build mode\n62: - **GIVEN** the `agent_metadata.yaml` contains `build_mode: cloud`\n63: - **WHEN** `build` command executes\n64: - **THEN** the system SHALL invoke `BuildRuntime._build_cloud()` to trigger a cloud-based build\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ### Requirement: Local Docker Build Prerequisites\n69: \n70: The system SHALL validate that Docker is available and running before attempting local builds.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Docker unavailable\n73: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n74: - **WHEN** Docker daemon is not running or not accessible\n75: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling with exit code 1\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Docker available\n78: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n79: - **WHEN** Docker daemon is running and accessible via `docker.from_env()`\n80: - **THEN** the system SHALL proceed with the Docker build process\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ### Requirement: Version Increment on Build\n85: \n86: The system SHALL automatically increment the agent version before each build and revert on failure.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Patch version bump for semantic version\n89: - **GIVEN** the metadata contains `version: \"1.2.3\"`\n90: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` is called during build\n91: - **THEN** the version SHALL be incremented to `\"1.2.4\"` (patch bump)\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Version increment with missing patch\n94: - **GIVEN** the metadata contains `version: \"1.2\"`\n95: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` is called\n96: - **THEN** the version SHALL be incremented by appending `.1` to become `\"1.2.1\"`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Version increment fallback for non-semver\n99: - **GIVEN** the metadata contains `version: \"beta-release\"`\n100: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` is called\n101: - **THEN** the version SHALL be incremented by appending `-1` to become `\"beta-release-1\"`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Revert version on build failure\n104: - **GIVEN** a build is in progress and version was incremented\n105: - **WHEN** the Docker build fails (e.g., Dockerfile not found, build error)\n106: - **THEN** the system SHALL revert the metadata version to its original value before the exception propagates\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ### Requirement: Docker Image Building\n111: \n112: The system SHALL build Docker images using the Docker SDK with proper tagging and build arguments.\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Build image from Dockerfile\n115: - **GIVEN** a packaged workspace with `Dockerfile` present\n116: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image()` is called with `dockerfile_path`, `context_path`, `image_name`, and `tag`\n117: - **THEN** the system SHALL build the image, tag it as `{image_name}:{tag}`, and return `{\"image_name\": str, \"image_id\": str, \"image_size\": str, \"build_time\": str}`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Build with proxy build arguments\n120: - **GIVEN** a proxy URL is provided via `--proxy`\n121: - **WHEN** the Docker build executes\n122: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass `build_args` including `HTTP_PROXY`, `HTTPS_PROXY`, and `NO_PROXY` to `DockerService.build_image()`\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: Build with image tag from version\n125: - **GIVEN** the incremented version is `\"1.2.4\"` and agent name is `\"my-agent\"`\n126: - **WHEN** the Docker build executes\n127: - **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `my-agent:1.2.4`\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: Cloud Build Integration\n132: \n133: The system SHALL support cloud-based builds through provider-specific implementations.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Cloud build with provider configuration\n136: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` and `--cloud-provider huawei` is specified\n137: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud()` is invoked\n138: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the cloud provider SDK to trigger a remote build with the workspace context\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Cloud build returns artifacts\n141: - **GIVEN** a cloud build completes successfully\n142: - **WHEN** `_build_cloud()` returns\n143: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `image_url`, `image_digest`, `build_id`, and `build_time`\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### Requirement: Build Metadata Update\n148: \n149: The system SHALL persist build results to the workspace metadata after successful builds.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Update metadata after successful build\n152: - **GIVEN** a local build completed successfully with image `my-agent:1.2.4`\n153: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata()` is called\n154: - **THEN** the `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be updated with `image.name`, `image.tag`, `image.id`, `image.size`, `build.time`, and `build.status = \"success\"`\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Update metadata with tag override\n157: - **GIVEN** a build result and explicit tag `\"latest\"`\n158: - **WHEN** `_update_build_metadata()` is called with `tag=\"latest\"`\n159: - **THEN** the metadata SHALL record the tag as `\"latest\"` regardless of version\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ### Requirement: Build Error Handling\n164: \n165: The system SHALL handle build errors gracefully with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Build with missing Dockerfile\n168: - **GIVEN** the workspace has no `Dockerfile` and pack was not run\n169: - **WHEN** `build` command executes\n170: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating missing Dockerfile and exit with code 1\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Build with invalid workspace\n173: - **GIVEN** the workspace path does not exist\n174: - **WHEN** `build` command executes\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message about invalid workspace path\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Build failure with verbose output\n178: - **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube build --verbose`\n179: - **WHEN** a build error occurs\n180: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error building agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code 1\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Build failure without verbose output\n183: - **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube build` without verbose flag\n184: - **WHEN** a build error occurs\n185: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error building agent: {e}` in red and exit with code 1 without traceback\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: Build Command Integration with Pack\n190: \n191: The system SHALL ensure build command works correctly with pre-packaged workspaces.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Build after successful pack\n194: - **GIVEN** the user has run `agentcube pack` successfully in the workspace\n195: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build`\n196: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the generated `Dockerfile` and `agent_metadata.yaml` from the pack operation\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Build requires pack metadata\n199: - **GIVEN** the workspace has no `agent_metadata.yaml`\n200: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build`\n201: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating that `pack` must be run first\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Interface Specification\n206: \n207: ### Command Signature\n208: \n209: ```python\n210: def build(\n211:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n212:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n213:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n214:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n215:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n216: ) -> None:\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### Runtime Interface\n220: \n221: ```python\n222: class BuildRuntime:\n223:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n224:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n225:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n226:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n227:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n228:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n229:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n230: ```\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ## File Index\n235: \n236: | Path | Purpose |\n237: |------|---------|\n238: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `build` command definition |\n239: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` class implementation |\n240: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` for local image building |\n241: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for metadata persistence |\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ## Dependencies\n246: \n247: | Dependency | Purpose |\n248: |------------|---------|\n249: | `typer` | CLI framework for command definition |\n250: | `docker` | Docker SDK for Python image building |\n251: | `pydantic` | Data validation for metadata models |\n252: | `pyyaml` | YAML serialization for metadata files |\n253: | `rich` | Rich text output and progress spinners |\n254: | `packaging` | Version parsing and incrementing |\n255: | `semver` | Semantic versioning support |\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ## Output Format\n260: \n261: ### Success Output\n262: \n263: ```\n264: Building agent [agent_name]...\n265: Version: [version] -> [incremented_version]\n266: Build mode: [local|cloud]\n267: \n268: ✓ Build completed successfully!\n269: \n270: Image: [image_name]:[tag]\n271: Image ID: [image_id]\n272: Image Size: [image_size]\n273: Build Time: [build_time]s\n274: \n275: Metadata updated: [metadata_path]\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### Error Output\n279: \n280: ```\n281: Building agent [agent_name]...\n282: \n283: Error building agent: [error_message]\n284: \n285: [traceback if verbose]\n286: ```\n287: \n288: ---\n289: \n290: ## Exit Codes\n291: \n292: | Code | Meaning |\n293: |------|---------|\n294: | 0 | Build successful |\n295: | 1 | Build failed (error message printed) |\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## Integration Points\n300: \n301: | Component | Integration |\n302: |-----------|-------------|\n303: | `pack` command | Must be run before `build` to generate Dockerfile |\n304: | `publish` command | Uses build output (image) for deployment |\n305: | `DockerService` | Called by `BuildRuntime._build_local()` |\n306: | `MetadataService` | Used to load/save `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n307: | `AgentMetadata` | Pydantic model for version and image tracking |\n\n(End of file - total 307 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-021  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nThe `build` command is responsible for building container images from packaged agent workspaces. It supports both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds, with automatic version increment and metadata management.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CLI Build Options\n\nThe system SHALL expose a `build` subcommand with configurable options for workspace path, proxy settings, cloud provider selection, and output directory.\n\n#### Scenario: Build with default options","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec-cli-build.md","time":{"start":1775888592325,"end":1775888592350}}}}
