{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888599876,"sessionID":"ses_284cacf3fffe6Xn9b7u593hknQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3585ba0010Hukfd27yvt7nU","messageID":"msg_d7b357e33001YqVcA4FntJ2g8g","sessionID":"ses_284cacf3fffe6Xn9b7u593hknQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: > **AR ID:** AR-021  \n4: > **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n5: > **Language:** Python  \n6: > **Size:** M  \n7: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: The `build` command builds a container image from the packaged agent workspace. It supports both local Docker builds and cloud-based build services. The command validates the workspace has been packed, loads metadata, determines the appropriate build strategy, executes the build process, and updates metadata with build results.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-4.1 — Build Models & Options\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 4.1.1 | Create `BuildOptions` dataclass in `agentcube/models/build_models.py` | Fields: proxy, cloud_provider, output, verbose; `from_options()` classmethod works | 0.5h |\n22: | 4.1.2 | Create `BuildResult` dataclass with build metadata | Fields: status, image_name, image_tag, build_timestamp, build_duration, logs_path | 0.5h |\n23: | 4.1.3 | Add `BuildStatus` enum (PENDING, BUILDING, SUCCESS, FAILED) | Enum values accessible; can serialize to string | 0.25h |\n24: | 4.1.4 | Update `agentcube/models/__init__.py` to export build models | BuildOptions, BuildResult, BuildStatus importable | 0.25h |\n25: \n26: **Deliverable:** Build models defined and exportable.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## ST-4.2 — BuildRuntime Core\n31: \n32: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n33: |---|------|--------------|------|\n34: | 4.2.1 | Update `BuildRuntime.__init__()` with MetadataService | Service instantiated; logger configured | 0.5h |\n35: | 4.2.2 | Implement `BuildRuntime.build()` main entry point | Returns BuildResult with all required fields | 1h |\n36: | 4.2.3 | Implement `BuildRuntime._validate_workspace_packed()` | Checks for agent_metadata.yaml; raises if not packed | 0.5h |\n37: | 4.2.4 | Implement `BuildRuntime._load_build_metadata()` | Loads metadata using MetadataService | 0.5h |\n38: | 4.2.5 | Implement `BuildRuntime._determine_build_strategy()` | Returns \"local\" or \"cloud\" based on metadata.build_mode | 0.5h |\n39: | 4.2.6 | Implement `BuildRuntime._prepare_build_context()` | Validates Dockerfile exists; returns build context path | 0.5h |\n40: | 4.2.7 | Implement `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata()` | Sets build_timestamp, build_status, image info; saves metadata | 0.5h |\n41: | 4.2.8 | Implement `BuildRuntime._prepare_output_path()` | Returns Path; creates directory if needed | 0.5h |\n42: \n43: **Deliverable:** BuildRuntime core methods implemented.\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## ST-4.3 — Local Build Implementation\n48: \n49: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n50: |---|------|--------------|------|\n51: | 4.3.1 | Implement `BuildRuntime._build_local()` dispatcher | Returns BuildResult; calls language-specific builder | 0.5h |\n52: | 4.3.2 | Implement `BuildRuntime._build_local_docker()` | Uses subprocess to call `docker build`; captures output | 1h |\n53: | 4.3.3 | Implement `BuildRuntime._generate_image_tag()` | Format: `{agent_name}:{version}` or `{agent_name}:latest` | 0.5h |\n54: | 4.3.4 | Implement `BuildRuntime._parse_dockerfile_language()` | Reads Dockerfile; detects FROM image to confirm language | 0.5h |\n55: | 4.3.5 | Handle Docker not installed error | Raises RuntimeError with clear message if docker command fails | 0.5h |\n56: | 4.3.6 | Handle Docker build failure | Captures exit code; raises BuildError with logs | 0.5h |\n57: | 4.3.7 | Save build logs to output path | Writes docker build output to `{output}/build.log` | 0.5h |\n58: \n59: **Deliverable:** Local Docker build works end-to-end.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## ST-4.4 — Cloud Build Implementation (Stub)\n64: \n65: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n66: |---|------|--------------|------|\n67: | 4.4.1 | Implement `BuildRuntime._build_cloud()` dispatcher | Returns BuildResult; validates cloud_provider | 0.5h |\n68: | 4.4.2 | Implement `BuildRuntime._build_cloud_huawei()` stub | Logs \"Cloud build not yet implemented\"; returns pending status | 0.5h |\n69: | 4.4.3 | Validate cloud_provider is supported | Raises ValueError if provider not in supported list | 0.25h |\n70: | 4.4.4 | Handle missing cloud credentials | Raises AuthenticationError if credentials not configured | 0.5h |\n71: \n72: **Deliverable:** Cloud build stub implemented with proper validation.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## ST-4.5 — Proxy & Network Configuration\n77: \n78: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n79: |---|------|--------------|------|\n80: | 4.5.1 | Implement `BuildRuntime._configure_proxy()` | Sets HTTP_PROXY, HTTPS_PROXY env vars for build | 0.5h |\n81: | 4.5.2 | Implement `BuildRuntime._get_docker_build_args()` | Returns list of --build-arg for proxy settings | 0.5h |\n82: | 4.5.3 | Pass proxy config to local Docker build | Docker build command includes proxy build args | 0.5h |\n83: | 4.5.4 | Validate proxy URL format | Raises ValueError if proxy URL is malformed | 0.5h |\n84: \n85: **Deliverable:** Proxy configuration works for local builds.\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## ST-4.6 — CLI Integration\n90: \n91: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n92: |---|------|--------------|------|\n93: | 4.6.1 | Update `build` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Remove \"not yet implemented\" stub | 0.25h |\n94: | 4.6.2 | Wire build command to BuildRuntime | Instantiates runtime; calls build(); handles errors | 0.5h |\n95: | 4.6.3 | Add Rich progress spinner during build | Progress indicator shown during build operation | 0.5h |\n96: | 4.6.4 | Format success message with image info | Prints image_name, image_tag, build_duration on success | 0.5h |\n97: | 4.6.5 | Format failure message with logs path | Prints error and logs location on failure | 0.5h |\n98: | 4.6.6 | Handle BuildRuntime exceptions in `_handle_error()` | Error messages displayed in red; traceback if verbose | 0.5h |\n99: \n100: **Deliverable:** CLI build command works end-to-end with proper UI.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## ST-4.7 — Error Handling & Exceptions\n105: \n106: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n107: |---|------|--------------|------|\n108: | 4.7.1 | Create `BuildError` exception class | Inherits from RuntimeError; accepts message and logs | 0.5h |\n109: | 4.7.2 | Create `WorkspaceNotPackedError` exception class | Raised when agent_metadata.yaml missing | 0.5h |\n110: | 4.7.3 | Create `DockerNotFoundError` exception class | Raised when docker command not available | 0.5h |\n111: | 4.7.4 | Create `AuthenticationError` exception class | Raised when cloud credentials missing | 0.5h |\n112: | 4.7.5 | Add exception classes to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | All exceptions exportable from runtime package | 0.25h |\n113: \n114: **Deliverable:** Custom exceptions defined and used appropriately.\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## ST-4.8 — Unit Tests — Build Models\n119: \n120: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n121: |---|------|--------------|------|\n122: | 4.8.1 | Write `TestBuildOptions` — creation with all fields | Options object created correctly | 0.5h |\n123: | 4.8.2 | Write `TestBuildOptions` — from_options filtering | None values filtered; non-None values preserved | 0.5h |\n124: | 4.8.3 | Write `TestBuildResult` — creation with all fields | Result object created correctly | 0.5h |\n125: | 4.8.4 | Write `TestBuildStatus` — enum values | PENDING, BUILDING, SUCCESS, FAILED accessible | 0.5h |\n126: | 4.8.5 | Write `TestBuildStatus` — serialization | str(status) returns expected value | 0.25h |\n127: \n128: **Deliverable:** Model tests pass with >80% coverage.\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## ST-4.9 — Unit Tests — BuildRuntime Core\n133: \n134: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n135: |---|------|--------------|------|\n136: | 4.9.1 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — initialization | Creates logger and MetadataService | 0.5h |\n137: | 4.9.2 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — validate workspace packed | WorkspaceNotPackedError if no metadata | 0.5h |\n138: | 4.9.3 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — load build metadata | Loads from agent_metadata.yaml | 0.5h |\n139: | 4.9.4 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — determine local strategy | Returns \"local\" when build_mode=local | 0.5h |\n140: | 4.9.5 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — determine cloud strategy | Returns \"cloud\" when build_mode=cloud | 0.5h |\n141: | 4.9.6 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — prepare build context | Returns path; validates Dockerfile exists | 0.5h |\n142: | 4.9.7 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — build context missing Dockerfile | Raises FileNotFoundError | 0.5h |\n143: | 4.9.8 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — prepare output path | Creates directory; returns Path | 0.5h |\n144: | 4.9.9 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — generate image tag | Format: name:version or name:latest | 0.5h |\n145: | 4.9.10 | Write `TestBuildRuntime` — update build metadata | Sets timestamp, status, image info | 0.5h |\n146: \n147: **Deliverable:** BuildRuntime core tests pass with >80% coverage.\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ## ST-4.10 — Unit Tests — Local Build\n152: \n153: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n154: |---|------|--------------|------|\n155: | 4.10.1 | Write `TestLocalBuild` — docker build success | Returns SUCCESS status; correct image tag | 1h |\n156: | 4.10.2 | Write `TestLocalBuild` — docker build failure | Returns FAILED status; captures logs | 1h |\n157: | 4.10.3 | Write `TestLocalBuild` — docker not found | Raises DockerNotFoundError | 0.5h |\n158: | 4.10.4 | Write `TestLocalBuild` — parse dockerfile language | Detects Python FROM image correctly | 0.5h |\n159: | 4.10.5 | Write `TestLocalBuild` — parse dockerfile language Java | Detects Java FROM image correctly | 0.5h |\n160: | 4.10.6 | Write `TestLocalBuild` — proxy configuration | Build args include proxy settings | 0.5h |\n161: | 4.10.7 | Write `TestLocalBuild` — save build logs | Log file created in output path | 0.5h |\n162: | 4.10.8 | Write `TestLocalBuild` — build duration tracking | Duration > 0 in BuildResult | 0.5h |\n163: \n164: **Deliverable:** Local build tests pass with >80% coverage.\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## ST-4.11 — Unit Tests — Cloud Build\n169: \n170: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n171: |---|------|--------------|------|\n172: | 4.11.1 | Write `TestCloudBuild` — unsupported provider | Raises ValueError for unknown provider | 0.5h |\n173: | 4.11.2 | Write `TestCloudBuild` — huawei stub returns pending | Returns PENDING status | 0.5h |\n174: | 4.11.3 | Write `TestCloudBuild` — missing credentials | Raises AuthenticationError | 0.5h |\n175: \n176: **Deliverable:** Cloud build tests pass with >80% coverage.\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## ST-4.12 — Unit Tests — CLI\n181: \n182: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n183: |---|------|--------------|------|\n184: | 4.12.1 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — default options | workspace=\".\", verbose=False | 0.5h |\n185: | 4.12.2 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — workspace override | -f /path/to/agent passed correctly | 0.5h |\n186: | 4.12.3 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — proxy option | -p http://proxy:8080 passed correctly | 0.5h |\n187: | 4.12.4 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — cloud provider option | --cloud-provider huawei passed correctly | 0.5h |\n188: | 4.12.5 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — output option | --output /build/output passed correctly | 0.5h |\n189: | 4.12.6 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — error handling non-verbose | Prints error, no traceback, exit 1 | 0.5h |\n190: | 4.12.7 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — error handling verbose | Prints error + traceback, exit 1 | 0.5h |\n191: | 4.12.8 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — success output | Success message with image info displayed | 0.5h |\n192: | 4.12.9 | Write `TestCLIBuild` — failure output | Failure message with logs path displayed | 0.5h |\n193: \n194: **Deliverable:** CLI tests pass with >80% coverage.\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## ST-4.13 — Integration Tests\n199: \n200: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n201: |---|------|--------------|------|\n202: | 4.13.1 | Create `tests/integration/test_build.py` with fixtures | Temp directories with packed Python/Java agents | 1h |\n203: | 4.13.2 | Test complete Python local build workflow | Valid workspace → image built → metadata updated | 2h |\n204: | 4.13.3 | Test complete Java local build workflow | Valid workspace → image built → metadata updated | 2h |\n205: | 4.13.4 | Test build with existing metadata | Build info merged with existing metadata | 0.5h |\n206: | 4.13.5 | Test build with CLI proxy override | Proxy settings applied to build | 0.5h |\n207: | 4.13.6 | Test build failure — workspace not packed | Error message displayed, exit code 1 | 0.5h |\n208: | 4.13.7 | Test build failure — missing Dockerfile | Error message displayed, exit code 1 | 0.5h |\n209: | 4.13.8 | Test verbose mode output | DEBUG logs visible during operation | 0.5h |\n210: \n211: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real filesystem operations.\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ## ST-4.14 — Documentation\n216: \n217: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n218: |---|------|--------------|------|\n219: | 4.14.1 | Add module docstring to `agentcube/models/build_models.py` | Clear description of build models | 0.5h |\n220: | 4.14.2 | Document `BuildOptions` fields with descriptions | Each field documented | 0.25h |\n221: | 4.14.3 | Document `BuildResult` fields with descriptions | Each field documented | 0.25h |\n222: | 4.14.4 | Add docstrings to `BuildRuntime` methods | Args, returns, raises documented | 0.5h |\n223: | 4.14.5 | Document exception classes | Purpose and usage documented | 0.25h |\n224: \n225: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for maintainers.\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ## Summary\n230: \n231: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n232: |-------|-------|------------|\n233: | ST-4.1: Build Models | 4 | 1.5h |\n234: | ST-4.2: BuildRuntime Core | 8 | 5h |\n235: | ST-4.3: Local Build | 7 | 4.5h |\n236: | ST-4.4: Cloud Build | 4 | 1.75h |\n237: | ST-4.5: Proxy Configuration | 4 | 2h |\n238: | ST-4.6: CLI Integration | 6 | 2.75h |\n239: | ST-4.7: Error Handling | 5 | 2.25h |\n240: | ST-4.8: Unit Tests — Models | 5 | 2.25h |\n241: | ST-4.9: Unit Tests — BuildRuntime Core | 10 | 5h |\n242: | ST-4.10: Unit Tests — Local Build | 8 | 4h |\n243: | ST-4.11: Unit Tests — Cloud Build | 3 | 1.5h |\n244: | ST-4.12: Unit Tests — CLI | 9 | 4h |\n245: | ST-4.13: Integration Tests | 8 | 7h |\n246: | ST-4.14: Documentation | 5 | 1.75h |\n247: | **Total** | **86** | **45.25h** |\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n252: \n253: - [ ] `agentcube/models/build_models.py` — BuildOptions, BuildResult, BuildStatus\n254: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` — BuildRuntime implementation (updated)\n255: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/exceptions.py` — BuildError, WorkspaceNotPackedError, DockerNotFoundError, AuthenticationError\n256: - [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — Build command implementation (updated)\n257: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_build_models.py` — Build model unit tests\n258: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_build_runtime.py` — BuildRuntime unit tests\n259: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_cli_build.py` — Build CLI unit tests\n260: - [ ] `tests/integration/test_build.py` — Build integration tests\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Verification Commands\n265: \n266: ```bash\n267: # Import verification\n268: python -c \"from agentcube.models.build_models import BuildOptions, BuildResult, BuildStatus\"\n269: python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\"\n270: python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.exceptions import BuildError, WorkspaceNotPackedError\"\n271: \n272: # CLI entry point verification\n273: kubectl-agentcube build --help\n274: \n275: # Unit test verification\n276: pytest tests/unit/test_build_models.py -v\n277: pytest tests/unit/test_build_runtime.py -v\n278: pytest tests/unit/test_cli_build.py -v\n279: \n280: # Integration tests\n281: pytest tests/integration/test_build.py -v\n282: \n283: # Coverage report\n284: pytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n285: \n286: # Lint verification\n287: ruff check agentcube/\n288: mypy agentcube/\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ---\n292: \n293: ## Definition of Done\n294: \n295: - [ ] All 86 tasks complete\n296: - [ ] Build command works end-to-end (`kubectl-agentcube build`)\n297: - [ ] Local Docker build produces working images\n298: - [ ] Cloud build stub implemented with validation\n299: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for each module)\n300: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n301: - [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n302: - [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n303: - [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Dependencies\n308: \n309: - `docker` — Docker CLI must be installed for local builds\n310: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` — CLI framework\n311: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation\n312: - `pyyaml>=6.0` — YAML parsing\n313: - `rich>=13.0.0` — Progress indicators and output\n314: - `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework\n315: - `pytest-cov>=4.1.0` — Coverage reporting\n316: - `pytest-mock>=3.11.0` — Mocking utilities\n317: \n318: ---\n319: \n320: ## Design Notes\n321: \n322: - **Build strategy:** Determined by metadata.build_mode (local/cloud)\n323: - **Local build:** Uses `docker build` subprocess with proper error handling\n324: - **Cloud build:** Stub implementation for future providers (huawei, aws, gcp)\n325: - **Image tagging:** `{agent_name}:{version}` or `{agent_name}:latest` if no version\n326: - **Proxy support:** HTTP_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY passed as build args\n327: - **Build logs:** Saved to `{output}/build.log` for troubleshooting\n328: - **Metadata update:** Sets build_timestamp, build_status, image info\n329: - **Error handling:** Specific exceptions for different failure modes\n330: - **Workspace validation:** Requires pack to have been run first (agent_metadata.yaml)\n331: \n332: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 332 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-021  \n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n> **Language:** Python  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `build` command builds a container image from the packaged agent workspace. It supports both local Docker builds and cloud-based build services. The command validates the workspace has been packed, loads metadata, determines the appropriate build strategy, executes the build process, and updates metadata with build results.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Build Models & Options\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775888599852,"end":1775888599872}}}}
