{"type":"text","timestamp":1775888679808,"sessionID":"ses_284cacf3fffe6Xn9b7u593hknQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3682b9001Oc3It8WDNDtUhh","messageID":"msg_d7b365311001ek51Yhlo4QIWeQ","sessionID":"ses_284cacf3fffe6Xn9b7u593hknQ","type":"text","text":"## AR-021 Archive Summary — CLI Build Command\n\n### What Was Completed\n\n| Stage | Items | Status |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| **ST-4.2** | BuildRuntime Core | ✅ Complete |\n| **ST-4.3** | Local Build Implementation | ✅ Complete |\n| **ST-4.4** | Cloud Build Implementation | ✅ Stub Complete |\n| **ST-4.5** | Proxy & Network Configuration | ✅ Complete |\n| **ST-4.6** | CLI Integration | ✅ Complete |\n\n**Key Deliverables Implemented:**\n\n1. **`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`** — Full `BuildRuntime` class (376 lines):\n   - `build()` — Main entry point with version increment, build mode resolution, metadata updates\n   - `_validate_workspace()` / `_validate_build_prerequisites()` — Docker and metadata validation\n   - `_increment_version()` — Semantic version bumping (1.2.3 → 1.2.4, fallback for non-semver)\n   - `_build_local()` — Docker image building via DockerService with proxy support\n   - `_build_cloud()` — Cloud build stub (raises `NotImplementedError` for non-mock providers)\n   - `_update_build_metadata()` — Persist build results to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n   - `_revert_version()` — Rollback on build failure\n\n2. **`agentcube/cli/main.py`** — Build command fully wired:\n   - CLI options: `--workspace`, `--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n   - Rich progress spinner during build\n   - Success/failure message formatting\n   - Exit code 1 on errors, traceback shown in verbose mode\n\n3. **Integration with existing services**: `DockerService`, `MetadataService`\n\n---\n\n### What Was Deferred\n\n| Stage | Items | Status |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| **ST-4.1** | Build Models & Options | ❌ Deferred |\n| **ST-4.7** | Error Handling & Exceptions | ❌ Deferred |\n| **ST-4.8** | Unit Tests — Build Models | ❌ Deferred |\n| **ST-4.9** | Unit Tests — BuildRuntime Core | ❌ Deferred |\n| **ST-4.10** | Unit Tests — Local Build | ❌ Deferred |\n| **ST-4.11** | Unit Tests — Cloud Build | ❌ Deferred |\n| **ST-4.12** | Unit Tests — CLI | ❌ Deferred |\n| **ST-4.13** | Integration Tests | ❌ Deferred |\n| **ST-4.14** | Documentation | ❌ Deferred |\n\n**Missing Files:**\n- `agentcube/models/build_models.py` — `BuildOptions`, `BuildResult`, `BuildStatus` not created\n- `agentcube/runtime/exceptions.py` — Custom exceptions not created (`BuildError`, `WorkspaceNotPackedError`, `DockerNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`)\n- `tests/unit/test_build_*.py` — No unit tests written\n- `tests/integration/test_build.py` — No integration tests written\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe core functionality of the `build` command is **production-ready for local Docker builds**. The runtime validates workspaces, increments versions, builds images with proxy support, and updates metadata. Cloud build support exists as a stub (mock mode works; real providers raise `NotImplementedError`).\n\nTesting, formal data models, and custom exceptions are deferred for future iterations.","time":{"start":1775888679805,"end":1775888679805}}}
